# Web servers works:-
  
  1. Run Server --> Create server & listen the incoming request.
  2. Bussines logic --> Handle requests, validate Input, Connect to Database.
  3. Response --> Return responses(Rendered HTML, JSON...).
  
 NodeJS project steps:-
 
 1. Create server using express, nodemon, body-parser.
 2. Crete EJS template(HTML Template) for user interaction.
 3. Routing between files and folders
 4. Make MVC architecture( model, view, controller)
 # model help to maintain Data like fetch , save etc
 # view is used for templates and decoupled from your application code.
 # controller connecting models to view and contain in-between logic.
 
 5. Create Databse using Mongo-DB(Mongoose) framework.
